# {{alternative spelling of|en|bonnet}}
# {{lb|en|Scotland|New Zealand}} A style of [[flat cap]] traditionally made from [[wool]], commonly worn by farmers and country [[gentlemen]] in cool climates.

====Usage notes====
Under the name bunnet, the flat cap is often associated with the working class in Scotland. The tam o'shanter is similar, but has a toorie, or pompom, on its centre.

